title: Watch live as Japanese ispace aims to be first company to land cargo on the moon
summary: Japanese lunar exploration company ispace is attempting to land its first cargo mission on the moon on Tuesday, which would make it the first private entity to complete the feat.

title: NASA Announces Student Winners of Power to Explore Challenge
summary: NASA selected three winners out of nine finalists in the second annual Power to Explore Challenge, a national competition for elementary through high school students featuring the power of radioisotopes for space exploration.

title: Connecting the Dots | SES-Intelsat merger would face uphill regulatory struggle
summary: Plenty of operational synergies await SES and Intelsat if the world’s largest fixed satellite service providers can craft a merger able to clear regulatory scrutiny.

title: Hydrosat collects $20 million in investment and grants
summary: Hydrosat received $20 million in government grants and investment for its campaign to measure water stress in plants and other indicators of climate change.

title: Quantum Space moves up development of Ranger transfer vehicle
summary: Quantum Space is accelerating work on a transfer vehicle designed to take payloads to both geostationary orbit and cislunar space to support growing demand from commercial and government customers.

title: SpaceX delays latest Starlink Group 3 deployment launch
summary: SpaceX’s 27th launch of the year was set for Tuesday, April 25, 2023, lofting another batch of 46 Starlink satellites into low Earth orbit. However, the liftoff, scheduled to occur at 6:40 AM PDT (13:40 UTC) from Space Launch Complex 4 East (SLC-4E) at Vandenberg Space Force Base in California, was delayed before prop loading was set to take place.

title: Falcon Heavy delay affects space station manifest
summary: A delayed launch of commercial satellites on a Falcon Heavy could upend the schedule of flights to the International Space Station, including a private astronaut mission that was scheduled for early May.

title: SpaceX Receives Permission To Lease Historic SLC-6 At Vandenberg Space Force Base
summary: Vandenberg Space Force Base has granted SpaceX permission to lease Space Launch Complex 6 for Falcon rocket launches.

title: NASA InSight Study Provides Clearest Look Ever at Martian Core
summary: A pair of quakes in 2021 sent seismic waves deep into the Red Planet’s core, giving scientists the best data yet on its size and composition.

title: Ursa Major to supply upper-stage engine for Astra’s new rocket
summary: Rocket propulsion startup Ursa Major announced April 24 that Astra Space selected the company’s Hadley liquid engine to power the upper stage of its new Rocket 4 launch vehicle.
